West Virginia Aims To Test All Nursing Home Residents, Workers for COVID-19Enlarge this image toggle caption Chris Jackson/AP Chris Jackson/APUpdated at 6:44 p.m.
ETAmid growing concern about the well-being of residents of elder care facilities, West Virginia officials are preparing to test every nursing home resident and worker in the state for the new coronavirus.
The decision follows outbreaks at care centers nationwide, including multiple positive tests at a facility in Jackson County, W.Va., this week.
Elder care centers have been a major focus of concern as numerous outbreaks and deaths have occurred at such facilities.
